cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper is about Neural Machine Translation systems that incorporate visual features, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely, as the paper discusses the integration of visual features. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories, as they are broad areas that encompass NLP and computer vision. Finally, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible given the focus on multimodal translation.
